<plot>Bill was never lucky in love. But now a beautiful woman has thrown herself at his feet. The only problem is: She is his best friend's soon-to-be ex wife. Can Bill figure out a way to get the girl without losing his friend? This movie is the first film to explore the unwritten male code of conduct "The Code" which states it isn't cool to date your friends family members, or past girlfriends. A code which has always existed, but has rarely been followed. In this self-proclaimed "Dick Flick" (a film about relationships from the male perspective) we explore the boundaries of friendship and desire.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?117627</url></doc>
